text.tspan: The traffic is binding with the frequent stops, with the sidewalk construction,
with the pedestrians, with the constant mirror checking for the fuzz.
Tireless walking checking the door, are the roommates home? Should I
lock the door> Already to the car door, no time to think of such thoughts
The path is straight no need to concern my brain with cluttering thoughts about where to
go. Just follow the road and in due time you will park and begin the task of walking.
Grab my backpack occupying the passenger seat turn the
vehicle off. Check then recheck again to secure that my
essential everyday items are in their rightful places.
Carefully step from the safety of my vehicle that seems to sit
so low to the ground. Lock the door, forgetting that I have
already locked it I subconciously lock the vehicle a second
first spark of the morning takes
light giving in to my early day habitual
routine. The ember embraces from the center
stripping my percieved idea of health from the walls of my
body. I don’t condone my actions nor will I justify the
decisions I make for the benefit of others. My material form
is for the benefit of the concious form that inhabits this vessel.
Everything that is what makes me the individual
can’t be contested by any other voice. Every
mind is held responsible by the self.
Step it up, step it up.
